arned%20some%20valuable%20lessons%20about%20raising%20them.%20I%20wish%20someone%20had%20shared%20them%20with%20me%2C%20because%20not%20only%20can%20parenting%20teens%20be%20difficult%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20be%20shockingly%20lonely.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294e8f3f3-30eb-45f9-aa02-470a7a112fb3%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDoing%20and%20being%20their%20best%20matters%20most%2C%20not%20grades%20or%20looking%20a%20certain%20way%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20watched%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-school-teacher-shares-one-piece-of-advice-for-parents-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ekids%20struggle%20with%20grades%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20because%20certain%20subjects%20were%20harder%20or%20teachers%20graded%20differently.%20I've%20stood%20back%20and%20seen%20them%20wonder%20if%20they%20were%20too%20much%20of%20this%20or%20not%20enough%20of%20that.%20Were%20their%20clothes%20just%20right%3F%20What%20shoes%20would%20be%20best%3F%20How%20should%20they%20wear%20their%20hair%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWatching%20them%20grapple%20with%20these%20insecurities%20made%20me%20realize%20one%20thing%3A%20nothing%20truly%20matters%20as%20long%20as%20they%20are%20doing%20their%20best%20and%20being%20the%20best%20version%20of%20themselves%20that%20they%20can%20be.%20If%20they%20get%20a%20C%20in%20math%2C%20but%20they%20worked%20for%20it%2C%20it's%20fine.%20We%20all%20have%20our%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses.%20As%20long%20as%20they%20try%20their%20best%2C%20they've%20succeeded.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22532d00d0-4b10-4d95-a279-6737883c2180%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETeenagers'%20brains%20are%20not%20fully%20developed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20brain%20does%20not%20fully%20develop%20and%20mature%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nimh.nih.gov%2Fhealth%2Fpublications%2Fthe-teen-brain-7-things-to-know%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAlthough%2520the%2520brain%2520stops%2520growing%2Cthe%2520last%2520parts%2520to%2520mature.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20until%20your%2020s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Teenagers%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20they%20are%20and%20what%20boundaries%20they%20hold.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20bad%20thing%2C%20but%20it%20does%20mean%20sometimes%20the%20way%20we%20think%20as%20parents%20may%20not%20make%20sense%20to%20them%20and%20vice%20versa.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20experimentation%20at%20this%20age%20is%20scary%2C%20especially%20to%20parents%2C%20it%20is%20necessary%20and%20normal.%20While%20I%20don't%20always%20agree%20with%20my%20kids'%20decisions%2C%20I%20do%20try%20to%20view%20them%20without%20judgment%20and%20through%20their%20eyes.%20I%20think%20back%20to%20when%20I%20was%20a%20teenager.%20By%20remembering%20my%20teen%20years%20and%20some%20of%20the%20decisions%20I%20made%2C%20I%20am%20reminded%20not%20only%20of%20what%20it%20feels%20like%20to%20be%20in%20their%20shoes%20but%20also%20of%20how%20some%20of%20those%20decisions%20taught%20me%20valuable%20lessons%20about%20becoming%20an%20adult.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b9c808b-37b0-42bd-b579-4ecd13d10e3d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20the%20power%20to%20build%20up%20or%20tear%20down%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20things%20I%20say%20to%20my%20teens%20and%20the%20way%20I%20respond%20to%20them%20can%20help%20them%20build%20confidence%20or%20foster%20insecurities.%20My%20choices%20and%20words%20impact%20them.%20Modeling%20by%20showing%20them%20how%20we%20react%20and%20respond%20in%20situations%20is%20one%20of%20our%20most%20vital%20responsibilities.%20As%20parents%2C%20we%20show%20our%20kids%20how%20to%20behave%20and%20interact%20with%20people.%20What%20we%20say%20and%20do%20matters%2C%20especially%20to%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb61e8c5-f6b5-4e0b-aeb5-76c030fe8596%5C